---
layout: base.njk
isHome: true
description: "Ali Akbar Saleh Bigdeli — systems programming, performance, and practical engineering notes in Rust."
---
<main class="container">
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Ali Akbar Saleh Bigdeli</p>
    <h1>Notes on Rust programming</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A focused engineering blog about Rust patterns, async systems, error handling,
      and performance-minded design. Content is optimized for readable code-heavy posts.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="posts" class="posts-section">
    <h2>Latest Posts</h2>

    {%- for post in collections.postsSorted %}
    <article class="post-card">
      <div class="post-meta">
        <span>{{ post.date | formatPostDate }}</span>
        {% if post.data.category -%}
        <span class="tag">{{ post.data.category }}</span>
        {%- endif %}
        {% for t in post.data.postTags | default([]) -%}
        {% if loop.index0 < 2 %}<span class="tag">{{ t }}</span>{% endif %}
        {%- endfor %}
      </div>
      <h3><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h3>
      <p>{{ post.data.description }}</p>
    </article>
    {%- endfor %}
  </section>

  <section id="about" class="about">
    <h2>About This Blog</h2>
    <p>
      I write practical notes for developers shipping Rust in production.
      Expect short, actionable posts with real code examples.
    </p>
    <p>
      Want to subscribe? Use the <a href="/feed.xml">RSS feed</a>. Looking for specific topics?
      Browse <a href="/categories/">categories</a> or <a href="/tags/">tags</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      New post workflow: add a <code>src/posts/your-slug.md</code> file (start from
      <code>src/_templates/post-starter.md</code>), then run <code>npm run build</code>.
    </p>
  </section>
</main>
